      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Critical] Line 187: When every known node is in backoff, `getKnownNodesRandom()` returns an empty set and `maintainBuckets()` leaves the bucket underfilled until some external event calls it again. Since no retry timer is scheduled for `nextRetry`, a node whose backoff expires may never be retried, which breaks the intended exponential backoff behavior. Schedule maintenance for the earliest skipped retry time, or have this code arm an existing timer/event loop when filtered candidates are skipped.\n```suggestion\n// Track the earliest nextRetry among skipped nodes and schedule maintainBuckets()\n// for that time so backoff expiry causes an actual retry.\n````",
