      "message": "[🔴 Critical Issues] Line 354: This records a backoff failure for every null socket callback, but `needSocketCb_` can fail for reasons unrelated to the peer being unreachable, such as local network setup/resource failures, account shutdown races, or ICE/TURN allocation errors. In those cases this change suppresses otherwise reachable bootstrap nodes for up to 6 hours and can make swarm recovery much worse. Backoff should only be applied when the callback can distinguish a completed remote reachability failure from a local/transient setup failure, or the callback should pass an explicit failure reason. For example:\n```suggestion\nif (!noNewSocket \u0026\u0026 reason \u003d\u003d ConnectFailureReason::UnreachablePeer)\n    shared-\u003enoteConnectionFailure(nodeId);\n```",
